          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_bGK7z9": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Is BERO available internationally?",
            "open_collapsible": false,
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>We are currently available in the US and UK. Keep an eye out for updates on our website and social (<a href=\"https://instagram.com/berobrewing\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">@berobrewing</span></a>) for future markets.</p>",
            "page": "",
            "anchor": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_Y7jhAe": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Will I have to show ID when buying BERO in stores?",
            "open_collapsible": false,
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>This varies widely and will depend on your state's legislation. Some states have laws restricting the purchase of non-alcoholic beer to people 21 and older. For example, Ohio requires people to be at least 18 years old to buy non-alcoholic beer. Oregon, West Virginia, and Wyoming have similar laws for drinks with at least 0.5% ABV. Georgia considers NA beer as beer. Some retailers may also ask you for your ID.</p>",
            "page": "",
            "anchor": ""
          }
        }
      },
